  "description": [
    "CALCUTTA SUPREME COURJuxy 2 1828 THE MAGISTRATE OF ROOGHLY On His Lordship the Chief Justice coming into Court thisday he addressed himself to the Advo cate General and stated that a writ of assistance had been issued to the Sheriff some time since di recting him toput a person in possession of cer tain property The Sheriff in the usual way wrote to the Judge of the district of Hoogly in which the property was situated requesting him to assist the officers imthe discharge of their duties Tne Judge refused but the Sheriff being unwilling to subject him to legal proceedings wrote again stating that if the writ was returned in the usual way an attachment would be issned against him and at the same time urging him to have the necessary assistance rendered to the officer The Magistrate said his Lordship again refused and as we are as unwilling as the Sueriff to have legal steps taken we would wishi you Mr Advo cate Generalto make inquiries into the case be tween this and to morrow it pethaps may be necessary for usto have some communication with gove nment respecting it The Advocate General assented COURT OF REQUESTSJory 2"
  ],
